---
import LayoutFunnel from '@/layouts/LayoutFunnel.astro';
---

<LayoutFunnel title="MedTech Revenue Architecture | Marketing by Besic">
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="min-h-screen flex items-center justify-center py-20">
    <div class="container-custom max-w-4xl text-center">
      <div class="w-20 h-20 bg-brand/10 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-8">
        <svg class="w-10 h-10 text-brand" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M4.318 6.318a4.5 4.5 0 000 6.364L12 20.364l7.682-7.682a4.5 4.5 0 00-6.364-6.364L12 7.636l-1.318-1.318a4.5 4.5 0 00-6.364 0z" />
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 11v4m0 0h-2m2 0h2" />
        </svg>
      </div>

      <h1 class="heading-xl mb-6">
        Your Medical Device Has Better Science Than Market Share. We Fix That.
      </h1>
      <p class="body-lg mb-12">
        Superior clinical evidence doesn't sell itself. The market defaults to what it knows, not what's better. You need a positioning system that turns scientific advantage into commercial dominance.
      </p>

      <!-- Hero Image (placeholder: using clinics image until medtech-specific asset available) -->
      <img src="/offer-clinics-hero.webp" alt="MedTech Revenue Architecture (placeholder image)" class="w-full rounded-lg mb-12 object-cover max-h-[500px]" width="1200" height="500" loading="eager" />
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Problem Section -->
  <section class="py-20">
    <div class="container-custom max-w-3xl">
      <h2 class="heading-lg mb-8 text-center">Three Reasons Your Device Isn't Winning the Market</h2>

      <div class="space-y-8">
        <div class="bg-bg-secondary border border-white/5 rounded-xl p-8 text-left">
          <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold mb-3 text-brand">Leak 1: Brilliant Product, Broken Positioning</h3>
          <p class="body-md">
            The market doesn't understand why your device is different. Your R&D team knows the clinical evidence is superior. Your prospects don't. They see "another medical device" because your marketing communicates features, not paradigm shift. You're selling specifications when you should be selling the new standard of care.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-bg-secondary border border-white/5 rounded-xl p-8 text-left">
          <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold mb-3 text-brand">Leak 2: Entrenched Industry Bias</h3>
          <p class="body-md">
            Clinicians default to what they know, not what's better. Your competitor's device has been in the market for 10 years. Theirs is "safe." Yours is "new." In medical procurement, "new" means risk. Without a systematic strategy to reposition the incumbent as outdated, your superior science loses to inferior inertia.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-bg-secondary border border-white/5 rounded-xl p-8 text-left">
          <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold mb-3 text-brand">Leak 3: Trade Show Presence Without Systematic Follow-Up</h3>
          <p class="body-md">
            You invested EUR 50K in your MEDICA booth. You collected 200 business cards. Two weeks later, those leads are cold. No segmented nurture. No clinical evidence drip. No multi-touch follow-up calibrated to procurement timelines. Your trade show ROI dies in the spreadsheet.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Problem Image (placeholder: using clinics image) -->
      <img src="/offer-clinics-problem.webp" alt="MedTech positioning gap diagnosis (placeholder image)" class="w-full rounded-lg my-12 object-cover max-h-[300px]" width="1200" height="300" loading="lazy" />
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Solution Section -->
  <section class="py-20">
    <div class="container-custom max-w-3xl">
      <h2 class="heading-lg mb-8 text-center">The MedTech Market Dominance Architecture</h2>

      <!-- Phase 1 -->
      <div class="bg-bg-secondary border border-white/5 rounded-xl p-8 mb-6 text-left">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-brand/10 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
            <span class="text-brand font-bold">1</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold mb-2">Phase 1: Market Positioning Diagnostic</h3>
            <p class="body-md">
              We audit how you're perceived versus competitors and identify the perception gap. Clinician interviews. Competitor messaging analysis. Procurement decision mapping. You'll see exactly where your positioning fails to convert scientific superiority into commercial preference.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Phase 2 -->
      <div class="bg-bg-secondary border border-white/5 rounded-xl p-8 mb-6 text-left">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-brand/10 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
            <span class="text-brand font-bold">2</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold mb-2">Phase 2: B2B Authority Architecture</h3>
            <p class="body-md">
              Position your device as the new standard of care. Neurolinguistic copy that reframes the incumbent as outdated. Clinical evidence packaging designed for procurement committees, not researchers. Digital omnipresence across the channels where purchase decisions actually happen.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Phase 3 -->
      <div class="bg-bg-secondary border border-white/5 rounded-xl p-8 text-left">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-brand/10 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
            <span class="text-brand font-bold">3</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold mb-2">Phase 3: International Expansion System</h3>
            <p class="body-md">
              Replicate domestic success across international markets using multilingual campaigns (EN, DE, IT, FR). Market-specific regulatory positioning. Distributor recruitment architecture. KOL identification and engagement protocols calibrated to each market's clinical hierarchy.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Solution Image (placeholder: using clinics image) -->
      <img src="/offer-clinics-solution.webp" alt="MedTech Market Dominance Architecture system (placeholder image)" class="w-full rounded-lg my-12 object-cover max-h-[300px]" width="1200" height="300" loading="lazy" />
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Execution Gap Section -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-[#111111] relative z-10">
    <div class="container-custom max-w-3xl">
      <h2 class="heading-lg mb-8 text-center">Most Agencies Deliver Reports. We Deliver Market Share.</h2>
      <p class="body-md mb-6 text-center">
        The gap between having superior science and winning the market is where medical device companies stall for years. Your last marketing agency produced "awareness." Your market share didn't move. Our framework closes the execution gap by rebuilding your entire go-to-market architecture -- from clinical evidence packaging to international distributor acquisition.
      </p>
      <p class="body-md mb-6 text-center font-semibold text-brand">
        We positioned Micro Medico's needle-free fillers as the new standard of care. Domestic dominance in Slovenia, then international B2B acquisition across 21 countries.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA Section -->
  <section class="py-20 pb-48">
    <div class="container-custom max-w-3xl text-center">
      <h2 class="heading-lg mb-6">Apply for a Revenue Diagnosis</h2>
      <p class="body-lg mb-12">
        We work with medical device companies with proven clinical evidence and EUR 1M+ annual revenue who are ready to convert scientific advantage into market dominance. If that's you, apply below.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-12 flex justify-center w-full">
        <a
          href="/en/apply"
          class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-8 py-4 text-lg font-bold text-white transition-all duration-300 bg-[#8224e3] rounded-lg hover:bg-[#6a1ca6] hover:scale-105 shadow-[0_0_20px_rgba(130,36,227,0.4)]"
        >
          Apply for Revenue Diagnosis
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</LayoutFunnel>
